# Akshay & Nishitha Love Story Website 💕

A beautiful, interactive website celebrating the love story of Akshay and Nishitha.

## Features ✨

- **Beautiful Purple/Lavender Theme** - Romantic gradient background with glass-morphism effects
- **Divided Layout** - Left side for Akshay, right side for Nishitha
- **Interactive Buttons**:
  - 💋 **Kiss Button** - Changes background to kiss image with floating hearts animation
  - 🙏 **God Button** - Changes background to god blessing with sparkle effects
- **Responsive Design** - Works perfectly on all devices
- **Animated Elements** - Floating hearts, sparkles, and smooth transitions
- **Love Quotes** - Beautiful romantic quotes for both individuals
- **Special Message** - Bottom quote about long-distance love and future meetings

## How to Use 🚀

1. **Open the Website**: Double-click on `index.html` to open in your web browser
2. **Explore the Sections**: 
   - Top: Beautiful header with animated hearts
   - Left: Akshay's section with avatar and buttons
   - Right: Nishitha's section with avatar and buttons
   - Bottom: Inspirational quote about your love journey

3. **Try the Interactive Features**:
   - Click the **Kiss Button** 💋 to see floating hearts and background change
   - Click the **God Button** 🙏 to see sparkles and blessing effects
   - Watch the beautiful animations and effects

## File Structure 📁

```
Akshay-Nishitha-Love-Story/
├── index.html          # Main HTML file
├── styles.css          # Beautiful CSS styling
├── script.js           # Interactive JavaScript functionality
├── .gitignore          # Git ignore file
└── README.md           # This file
```

## GitHub Collaboration Setup 🐙

### Prerequisites
- Git installed on your system
- GitHub account

### Initial Setup (After Git Installation)
```bash
# Navigate to the project folder
cd "Akshay-Nishitha-Love-Story"

# Initialize Git repository
git init

# Add all files to Git
git add .

# Make initial commit
git commit -m "Initial commit: Akshay & Nishitha Love Story Website"

# Add GitHub remote (replace with your repository URL)
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/Akshay-Nishitha-Love-Story.git

# Push to GitHub
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
```

### Daily Collaboration Workflow
```bash
# Check status of changes
git status

# Add your changes
git add .

# Commit your changes
git commit -m "Description of your changes"

# Push to GitHub
git push

# Pull latest changes from collaborators
git pull origin main
```

### For Collaborators
```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/Akshay-Nishitha-Love-Story.git

# Navigate to project folder
cd Akshay-Nishitha-Love-Story

# Pull latest changes
git pull origin main
```

## Technical Details 🔧

- **HTML5** - Modern semantic structure
- **CSS3** - Advanced styling with gradients, animations, and glass-morphism
- **JavaScript ES6+** - Interactive functionality and dynamic effects
- **Responsive Design** - Mobile-friendly layout
- **Cross-browser Compatible** - Works on all modern browsers
- **Git Version Control** - Easy collaboration and version management

## Customization Options 🎨

You can easily customize:
- Colors and themes
- Text content and quotes
- Button styles and effects
- Animation timings
- Background images (replace emoji placeholders with actual images)

